4
00:00:12,660 --> 00:00:15,000
viewer discretion is advised]

5
00:00:15,240 --> 00:00:16,520
I have something to tell you.

6
00:00:17,840 --> 00:00:19,440
I don't know where to start.

7
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:22,320
When it's time,

8
00:00:22,660 --> 00:00:23,920
you'll know how to tell it to me.

9
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:26,960
This song

10
00:00:27,520 --> 00:00:28,720
It's for all of you.

11
00:00:29,920 --> 00:00:31,690
Where we put ourselves

12
00:00:31,720 --> 00:00:33,280
determines who we'll become.

13
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:36,540
Mom!

14
00:00:39,960 --> 00:00:41,360
How is your mother?

15
00:00:43,160 --> 00:00:43,920
Mom.

16
00:00:53,160 --> 00:00:53,880
Wake up.

17
00:00:55,360 --> 00:00:56,120
Hey!

18
00:00:56,920 --> 00:00:57,680
Wake up!

19
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:00,680
Wake up, now!

20
00:01:03,360 --> 00:01:04,080
Get up!

21
00:01:11,360 --> 00:01:13,320
You're such an impersonator.

22
00:01:14,060 --> 00:01:15,800
I shouldn't have trusted you.

23
00:01:16,420 --> 00:01:18,420
Get the hell out of my house, now!

24
00:01:19,160 --> 00:01:20,880
And don't you dare
show your face here again.

25
00:01:21,920 --> 00:01:23,610
What were you talking about
so loudly in the morning?

26
00:01:23,640 --> 00:01:24,600
Yeah.

27
00:01:24,740 --> 00:01:26,360
So loud that I could hear it
from downstairs.

28
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:28,960
Grandpa, Grandma,

29
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:31,120
this asshole has been deceiving us.

30
00:01:31,560 --> 00:01:32,960
He is one of the swindlers.

31
00:01:34,360 --> 00:01:36,759
That explains!
I've been wondering about that.

32
00:01:37,680 --> 00:01:39,280
I'm so disappointed.

33
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:41,640
I gave you my heart, Ritt.

34
00:01:41,740 --> 00:01:43,200
You fake fortune teller.

35
00:01:43,580 --> 00:01:45,080
How could you falsely claim
you're someone else?

36
00:01:46,039 --> 00:01:47,280
This guy is taken.

37
00:01:47,759 --> 00:01:49,400
You had the guts to claim him?

38
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:53,800
You impersonator.

39
00:01:54,080 --> 00:01:55,360
Get out of this house!

40
00:01:55,759 --> 00:01:57,360
Still acting confused?!

41
00:01:57,420 --> 00:01:58,440
Get out.

42
00:01:58,840 --> 00:01:59,680
Get out!

43
00:01:59,780 --> 00:02:00,650
Get out!

44
00:02:00,680 --> 00:02:02,010
Don't you hear that?! Get out!

45
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:02,770
- Get out!
- Sorry.

46
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:04,890
- Get out!
- Shameless!

47
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:06,610
- Don't touch me.
- Get out!

48
00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:07,520
- Get out!
- Leave!

49
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:09,380
Get out! Get out!

50
00:02:14,520 --> 00:02:18,320
♫Is it pure coincidence?♫

51
00:02:18,570 --> 00:02:22,640
♫Or is it destiny that decides?♫

52
00:02:22,670 --> 00:02:24,970
♫Is someone above drawing all these lines?♫

53
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:30,520
♫Or playing matchmaker in disguise?♫

54
00:02:31,140 --> 00:02:35,340
♫What if the stars shift in their place♫

55
00:02:35,530 --> 00:02:39,040
♫Slightly out of line,♫

56
00:02:39,770 --> 00:02:43,460
♫Will our orbits still align?♫

57
00:02:43,490 --> 00:02:47,800
♫Try answering if your world
will cross with mine♫

58
00:02:47,829 --> 00:02:51,880
♫Though the destiny between us
is differently defined♫

59
00:02:51,910 --> 00:02:57,160
♫And I believe our love has power♫

60
00:02:57,450 --> 00:03:01,300
♫I believe the love of us♫

61
00:03:01,330 --> 00:03:10,520
♫Will realign the stars back to the line
where they should be♫

62
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:13,140
It's time to wake up, Young Master Ritt.

63
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,560
Wake up.

64
00:03:19,100 --> 00:03:20,390
I'm sorry.

65
00:03:20,420 --> 00:03:21,730
I didn't mean to.

66
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:23,240
I'm so sorry.

67
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:25,320
Please don't push me away.

68
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:29,840
- I'm sorry.
- What's wrong with you?

69
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:33,990
What happened?

70
00:03:34,020 --> 00:03:35,280
Who pushed you away?

71
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:39,600
Did you just have a bad dream?

72
00:03:41,480 --> 00:03:42,600
You're grown up already.

73
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:44,520
It's nothing.

74
00:03:44,920 --> 00:03:46,240
You were just dreaming.

75
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:55,320
Can you promise me?

76
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:57,880
No matter what happens,

77
00:03:59,079 --> 00:04:01,640
please don't push me away from your life.

78
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:05,920
Can you promise me?

79
00:04:11,220 --> 00:04:12,640
I love you.

80
00:04:31,260 --> 00:04:33,000
Oh! Pitcha.

81
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:35,360
Why are you sleeping here?

82
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:38,080
Oh,

83
00:04:38,260 --> 00:04:39,760
so, who is this person?

84
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:41,480
He is Pure.

85
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:44,000
I thought it was too late last night,

86
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:46,200
so I told him to stay over here.

87
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:51,659
Why didn't you let him
sleep upstairs properly?

88
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:54,200
No problem, Mom.

89
00:04:54,380 --> 00:04:56,560
I can sleep anywhere. No worries.

90
00:04:56,960 --> 00:04:58,280
The sofa in this house

91
00:04:58,600 --> 00:05:00,000
is so soft.

92
00:05:01,320 --> 00:05:02,080
Okay.

93
00:05:02,220 --> 00:05:04,950
If you're already awake,
you can go take a shower upstairs,

94
00:05:04,980 --> 00:05:06,320
so we can have breakfast.

95
00:05:06,560 --> 00:05:07,940
Just washing my face is fine.

96
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:11,920
Taking a shower is fine.
It'll make you feel refreshed.

97
00:05:12,340 --> 00:05:13,920
You can do it in Pitcha's room

98
00:05:14,420 --> 00:05:16,380
and borrow his clothes first.

99
00:05:19,340 --> 00:05:20,400
Follow me.

100
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:43,680
I exclusively get into
a famous idol's room.

101
00:05:44,080 --> 00:05:45,720
It's such an honor for me.

102
00:05:46,159 --> 00:05:48,680
Didn't you just tell my mom that

103
00:05:48,780 --> 00:05:50,040
you slept well, huh?

104
00:05:50,140 --> 00:05:53,880
In front of your mom,
I should say that, shouldn't I?

105
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:55,520
Actually,

106
00:05:55,740 --> 00:05:58,640
I wanted to tell her so bad
that her son is mean.

107
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:00,400
He didn't want me
to sleep in his room.

108
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:01,560
Look,

109
00:06:01,860 --> 00:06:03,600
his bed can fit two people,

110
00:06:03,700 --> 00:06:06,720
but he let me sleep on the sofa
while having back pain for the whole night.

111
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:09,120
Just once.

112
00:06:12,900 --> 00:06:14,170
The bathroom is on that side.

113
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:15,800
I'm going to bring you a new toothbrush.

114
00:06:16,140 --> 00:06:18,360
And for the clothes,

115
00:06:18,540 --> 00:06:19,930
you just

116
00:06:19,960 --> 00:06:21,770
wear this for now, and your shirt...

117
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:22,480
Hey!

118
00:06:23,660 --> 00:06:24,680
What are you doing?

119
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:26,720
I'm just going to take a shower.

120
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,280
Have you done it?

121
00:06:31,980 --> 00:06:33,360
Do you want to do it again with me?

122
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:35,250
That's fine.

123
00:06:35,280 --> 00:06:36,640
Go right ahead.

124
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:37,760
Here.

125
00:06:41,159 --> 00:06:42,000
Go ahead.

126
00:06:56,630 --> 00:06:58,010
I thought you weren't going to eat.

127
00:06:58,040 --> 00:07:00,800
We're almost full now.

128
00:07:00,830 --> 00:07:02,960
- Go get them some more dim sum.
- Yes, sir.

129
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:08,120
What?

130
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:13,530
- Grandma.
- Hmm?

131
00:07:13,560 --> 00:07:16,480
Are there any tricks
to ward off bad dreams?

132
00:07:16,620 --> 00:07:18,020
What happened to you?
Do you have bad neck pain?

133
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:19,620
You must have got it
from sleeping the wrong way.

134
00:07:19,630 --> 00:07:20,490
Here.

135
00:07:20,520 --> 00:07:23,530
I have this green oil
for muscle relief.

136
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:25,580
It helps a lot. It's so nice.

137
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:27,530
No, it's not what you think, Grandpa.

138
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:28,160
Huh?

139
00:07:28,440 --> 00:07:30,880
I mean, how to ward off a bad dream.

140
00:07:31,020 --> 00:07:32,040
You're hard of hearing.

141
00:07:32,700 --> 00:07:34,640
Bad dream? Who had a bad dream? Is it you?

142
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:35,760
It's Ritt.

143
00:07:36,620 --> 00:07:38,120
His dream might be so real

144
00:07:38,159 --> 00:07:39,960
that he woke up early with tears.

145
00:07:40,340 --> 00:07:42,130
What did you dream about?

146
00:07:42,159 --> 00:07:45,570
They said you have to tell the elders
in the house about it.

147
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:47,600
After I listen to it, I'll say,

148
00:07:47,630 --> 00:07:49,130
"May the bad dream turn into a blessing."

149
00:07:49,159 --> 00:07:51,840
Then you'll have good luck. It's just that.

150
00:07:52,080 --> 00:07:53,440
Tell them.

151
00:07:58,840 --> 00:07:59,480
Uh...

152
00:08:00,430 --> 00:08:01,640
That's fine. That's fine.

153
00:08:01,700 --> 00:08:04,160
If you don't want to share it,
that's fine. Let's do this.

154
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:07,290
They say that
you should go to the bathroom.

155
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:09,250
Tell your bad dream,

156
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:12,650
then flush the toilet and let it go.

157
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:14,410
Tell it to the toilet.

158
00:08:14,440 --> 00:08:15,970
Or

159
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:18,030
pour the water into a water dipper,

160
00:08:18,060 --> 00:08:20,060
then tell everything to it.

161
00:08:20,090 --> 00:08:23,450
After that, just throw the water out.
That's all.

162
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:26,190
But don't tell anyone yet.

163
00:08:26,220 --> 00:08:27,760
Yeah, just try it.

164
00:08:37,799 --> 00:08:39,409
You've been coughing for many days.

165
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:41,520
I told you to see the doctor,
but you wouldn't listen.

166
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:44,480
I think you should go see the doctor, Grandpa.

167
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:46,450
I'm fine. It's just
because the weather is always changing.

168
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:49,650
Hot, cold, dusty, and a lot more.

169
00:08:49,680 --> 00:08:51,440
Everyone gets this. I'll be fine.

170
00:08:51,540 --> 00:08:54,040
So stubborn.
No matter what I say, he never listens.

171
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:56,560
I'll get well soon.

172
00:09:07,180 --> 00:09:09,480
Last night, I dreamed about...

173
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:11,880
You're such an impersonator.

174
00:09:12,280 --> 00:09:13,840
I shouldn't have trusted you.

175
00:09:14,740 --> 00:09:16,760
There was also Pitcha,
his real sweetheart.

176
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:18,200
This guy is taken.

177
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:20,160
You had the guts to claim him?

178
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:22,360
Those three feng shui masters...

179
00:09:22,660 --> 00:09:24,000
Get out of this house!

180
00:09:24,180 --> 00:09:26,210
You tricked him into loving you,
but you didn't take it seriously.

181
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:28,370
You said you cared about him,
but you took him for granted.

182
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:30,550
You're just a bad omen for this house.

183
00:09:30,580 --> 00:09:31,440
Get out!

184
00:09:32,780 --> 00:09:34,760
May it flow away without returning.

185
00:09:34,980 --> 00:09:36,200
Sadhu.

186
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:49,440
Smells so good. What are you cooking?

187
00:09:49,880 --> 00:09:51,570
Wait a minute. It's almost done.

188
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:52,600
Do you need some help?

189
00:09:53,760 --> 00:09:54,680
It's okay.

190
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:57,000
Just help me eat it, okay?

191
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:06,440
Hey, you!

192
00:10:07,040 --> 00:10:08,880
I just proved what the good smell is.

193
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:10,530
I thought it was the smell of food,

194
00:10:10,560 --> 00:10:12,880
but actually,
it was the smell of your cheeks.

195
00:10:13,040 --> 00:10:14,050
You're taking advantage of me.

196
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:16,440
If I told my mom what you did,
you'd definitely be in trouble.

197
00:10:17,900 --> 00:10:20,110
Is it done already? It smells so good.

198
00:10:20,140 --> 00:10:22,640
Almost done, Mom.
You can come down to wait now.

199
00:10:23,660 --> 00:10:24,920
Are these done?

200
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:26,280
I'll carry them there.

201
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:44,130
Take care of your health, Mom,

202
00:10:44,160 --> 00:10:45,340
so that you'll be healthy soon.

203
00:10:45,780 --> 00:10:47,040
I'll visit you next time.

204
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:48,680
Thank you.

205
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:13,000
Is Pure your friend from high school?

206
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:16,320
Pure...

207
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:19,440
is the owner of the bar
where you met me that night.

208
00:11:22,340 --> 00:11:23,400
I see.

209
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:27,000
A new friend.

210
00:11:28,060 --> 00:11:31,080
- Well, Pure...
- Get back to focusing on what you should do.

211
00:11:32,760 --> 00:11:33,400
Yes.

212
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:36,680
Now, I'm helping a group
of younger ones practice dancing.

213
00:11:36,780 --> 00:11:38,400
So, I got back to doing my practice, too.

214
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:41,570
But about singing that you caught me doing...

215
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:43,080
Consider it yourself

216
00:11:44,500 --> 00:11:46,880
if the things you did
are really good for you.

217
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:49,080
You're now grown up.

218
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:53,800
Yes, Mom.

219
00:11:57,020 --> 00:11:59,800
Don't let temporary pleasure

220
00:12:01,720 --> 00:12:05,360
make you forget everything
you've worked for your whole life.

221
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:23,570
I told you I'm fine.

222
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:25,360
I could even walk here myself.

223
00:12:25,560 --> 00:12:26,440
And...

224
00:12:26,780 --> 00:12:30,320
I have a bit of a sore throat and a cold
because I'm allergic to the weather.

225
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:32,560
Let me check more meticulously.

226
00:12:33,160 --> 00:12:35,840
Go ahead, doctor. To make it clear.

227
00:12:49,580 --> 00:12:52,040
Let me talk to you a bit
about your grandpa's symptoms.

228
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:02,080
[SCHOOL OF ARCHITECTURE,
ART, AND DESIGN]

229
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:17,160
[Ritt, the Prophecy Stone Master]

230
00:14:03,600 --> 00:14:07,240
[There is only one truth,
just as there is one true identity]

231
00:14:27,060 --> 00:14:30,360
A Chinese idiom says that...

232
00:14:34,980 --> 00:14:36,860
"Even though the sky is calm,

233
00:14:37,060 --> 00:14:39,320
there are still waves beneath the sea."

234
00:14:41,160 --> 00:14:42,300
Oh, why is our dining table's vibe...

235
00:14:42,330 --> 00:14:44,970
this quiet today?

236
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:48,000
Are there any waves under the sea here?

237
00:14:50,140 --> 00:14:52,490
Let's just talk about what's on your mind.

238
00:14:52,520 --> 00:14:54,850
We're in the same house.
Try to talk with each other.

239
00:14:54,880 --> 00:14:57,880
Don't stay quiet
and let your feelings carry you away.

240
00:15:00,560 --> 00:15:01,610
- Grandpa.
- Hmm?

241
00:15:01,640 --> 00:15:03,120
This chicken is yummy.

242
00:15:04,040 --> 00:15:06,890
You ate half the plate before telling me
it was yummy?

243
00:15:06,920 --> 00:15:09,530
- There you go. Eat up.
- That's enough.

244
00:15:09,560 --> 00:15:11,370
You keep serving him
until his plate is full.

245
00:15:11,400 --> 00:15:13,060
Can Ritt eat all of that?

246
00:15:13,180 --> 00:15:14,480
Let him gradually eat it.

247
00:15:17,880 --> 00:15:18,840
Why?

248
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:21,800
What did the doctor say at the hospital?

249
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:25,720
Did he tell you that I'm going to die?

250
00:15:26,440 --> 00:15:27,440
You're talking nonsense.

251
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:29,560
What you said makes no sense.

252
00:15:34,120 --> 00:15:35,520
You're still strong.

253
00:15:35,550 --> 00:15:37,280
You'll surely be with us for a long time.

254
00:15:37,340 --> 00:15:40,380
I'm strong,
but I need to be there again next week?

255
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:42,900
Isn't that strange?

256
00:15:44,620 --> 00:15:46,520
We need to follow up

257
00:15:46,680 --> 00:15:48,520
to see how much you've improved.

258
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:49,760
Mmm...

259
00:15:50,320 --> 00:15:52,840
If so, you don't have to worry.
Next week, we'll know.

260
00:15:52,870 --> 00:15:56,160
Let's have some conversations.
You guys are too quiet.

261
00:15:56,190 --> 00:15:58,360
Don't worry. I'll be fine.

262
00:16:14,880 --> 00:16:15,920
Still quiet, huh?

263
00:16:24,080 --> 00:16:26,320
Are you and Grandma
keeping some secrets from Grandpa?

264
00:16:28,560 --> 00:16:29,520
At the dining table,

265
00:16:30,180 --> 00:16:31,560
everyone seemed strange.

266
00:16:34,280 --> 00:16:35,280
It was nothing.

267
00:16:36,820 --> 00:16:38,000
That was so suspicious.

268
00:16:38,520 --> 00:16:39,680
Are you still saying it was nothing?

269
00:16:40,900 --> 00:16:42,520
It's about Grandpa's health.

270
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:44,240
It's nothing.

271
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:46,640
Okay.

272
00:16:47,700 --> 00:16:49,320
I know I'm an outsider,

273
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:51,680
not your family members.

274
00:16:53,530 --> 00:16:54,670
It's not like that.

275
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:56,840
- Well...
- It's fine.

276
00:16:59,260 --> 00:17:00,840
I know that

277
00:17:01,260 --> 00:17:02,680
it's none of my business.

278
00:17:04,160 --> 00:17:05,200
It's gone too far.

279
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:08,680
So, what's wrong with Grandpa?

280
00:17:11,800 --> 00:17:12,640
Cancer.

281
00:17:18,359 --> 00:17:19,040
So...

282
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:21,280
what did the doctor say?

283
00:17:21,619 --> 00:17:22,520
What stage is it?

284
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:30,320
It has spread everywhere.

285
00:17:31,360 --> 00:17:32,800
And what did the doctor suggest?

286
00:17:37,400 --> 00:17:38,440
Next week...

287
00:17:39,280 --> 00:17:42,640
He made an appointment with us to
talk about the treatment.

288
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:53,840
Nowadays,

289
00:17:54,620 --> 00:17:55,520
the doctors are talented.

290
00:17:57,160 --> 00:17:58,440
But no matter what,

291
00:17:59,740 --> 00:18:02,300
moral support is also important.

292
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:14,880
Thank you so much.

293
00:18:31,480 --> 00:18:33,800
[Magic Move]

294
00:18:44,360 --> 00:18:47,810
Magic Move isn't only
good at drinks and music,

295
00:18:47,840 --> 00:18:50,840
but there are also
two accurate fortune tellers here.

296
00:18:51,040 --> 00:18:53,410
And tonight is even more special

297
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:56,010
because the fortune tellers
are going to cast a spell

298
00:18:56,040 --> 00:18:58,630
in the special show for everyone tonight.

299
00:18:58,660 --> 00:19:00,960
Let's enjoy the show.

300
00:20:48,320 --> 00:20:49,160
What is this?

301
00:20:54,420 --> 00:20:55,440
Well,

302
00:20:55,640 --> 00:20:57,720
you thought you looked like the singer,

303
00:20:57,820 --> 00:20:59,720
so you danced to her song.

304
00:20:59,920 --> 00:21:03,200
Can I have some special tips
for my fortune teller-themed dance team?

305
00:21:03,340 --> 00:21:04,880
This is how you squeeze my money, right?

306
00:21:04,980 --> 00:21:08,200
It's called encouraging
the nation's youth, you know?

307
00:21:11,500 --> 00:21:13,760
Here, share it with everyone, okay?

308
00:21:17,880 --> 00:21:19,490
The mission of today is complete.

309
00:21:19,520 --> 00:21:21,350
Hey, everyone. Let's go back.

310
00:21:21,380 --> 00:21:23,380
And let's practice
at the same time tomorrow.

311
00:21:23,580 --> 00:21:24,930
But we need to take pictures first.

312
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:26,520
Join us, Pitcha.

313
00:21:31,480 --> 00:21:33,360
Over there, the customers are coming.
Take care of them.

314
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:36,360
Try to present... Oh.

315
00:21:38,060 --> 00:21:38,720
What?

316
00:21:39,420 --> 00:21:44,960
♫Happy birthday to you♫

317
00:21:45,120 --> 00:21:50,200
♫Happy birthday to you♫

318
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:56,760
♫Happy birthday, happy birthday♫

319
00:21:57,760 --> 00:22:06,160
♫Happy birthday to Pure♫

320
00:22:19,540 --> 00:22:20,400
Confused, huh?

321
00:22:20,420 --> 00:22:22,480
You're working so hard
that you forget your own birthday.

322
00:22:22,680 --> 00:22:24,160
Thank you, naughty sister.

323
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:26,160
Thank you, everyone.

324
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:29,920
And... Thank you so much.

325
00:22:32,600 --> 00:22:34,120
Wishing you all the happiness

326
00:22:34,720 --> 00:22:36,080
so that you can share some of it with me.

327
00:22:38,500 --> 00:22:40,040
It's Pure's birthday.

328
00:22:40,300 --> 00:22:42,080
We already had a show for you.

329
00:22:42,340 --> 00:22:44,800
Can you sing a song for him, Pitcha?

330
00:22:45,500 --> 00:22:46,240
Sure.

331
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:47,920
What song do you want?

332
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:49,720
What song do you want to listen to?

333
00:22:50,700 --> 00:22:52,380
Whatever you want to give it to me,

334
00:22:52,700 --> 00:22:53,580
just bring it on.

335
00:22:55,320 --> 00:22:56,040
Okay.

336
00:22:56,360 --> 00:22:58,360
Let's consider it your birthday gift

337
00:22:58,760 --> 00:23:01,320
because I just knew it was your birthday
when I entered the bar.

338
00:23:01,720 --> 00:23:03,120
I don't have anything to give you.

339
00:23:04,980 --> 00:23:06,240
Just you coming to my bar

340
00:23:06,880 --> 00:23:08,880
is already a gift to me.

341
00:23:15,780 --> 00:23:17,200
Something going on between you two?

342
00:23:17,840 --> 00:23:18,560
Hold it.

343
00:23:20,360 --> 00:23:21,400
Thank you.

344
00:23:25,340 --> 00:23:27,880
You must make yin and yang shake.

345
00:23:28,660 --> 00:23:31,050
I'm just coughing a little.

346
00:23:31,080 --> 00:23:33,680
You've been together for more than 30 years.

347
00:23:34,040 --> 00:23:36,070
The star line hasn't been changed.

348
00:23:36,100 --> 00:23:38,600
You must change it.

349
00:23:38,720 --> 00:23:40,630
No star is changing,

350
00:23:40,660 --> 00:23:42,570
but the weather is.
There is a lot of dust.

351
00:23:42,600 --> 00:23:43,960
That's why I cough.

352
00:23:44,020 --> 00:23:46,020
Strengthen love fate

353
00:23:46,180 --> 00:23:50,080
to support your health and good fortune.

354
00:23:50,320 --> 00:23:53,520
Really? Okay, fine.
Just tell us what we should do.

355
00:23:54,140 --> 00:23:56,000
You must get married!

356
00:23:56,040 --> 00:23:57,280
Get married?!

357
00:23:58,040 --> 00:24:00,010
Aiya...who will I marry?

358
00:24:00,040 --> 00:24:02,800
I'm this old,
so how can I find a new wife?

359
00:24:02,940 --> 00:24:05,370
You aren't stashing
a mistress anywhere else, are you?

360
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:08,850
- What? These guys told me to.
- Hey, just marry the same person.

361
00:24:08,880 --> 00:24:12,320
- Marrying the same person is fine.
- Aiya.

362
00:24:12,600 --> 00:24:15,800
Another wedding?
We just held a wedding last time.

363
00:24:15,830 --> 00:24:17,280
But this time,

364
00:24:17,600 --> 00:24:20,600
it's a wedding to strengthen his luck,

365
00:24:21,170 --> 00:24:23,250
so his health horoscope
will be good.

366
00:24:23,280 --> 00:24:24,930
No pain, no fever.

367
00:24:26,560 --> 00:24:27,760
That sounds reasonable.

368
00:24:44,440 --> 00:24:46,440
Bow to Heaven and Earth.

369
00:24:48,120 --> 00:24:49,880
Bow to the elders.

370
00:24:54,040 --> 00:24:56,540
Bow to each other.

371
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:02,880
Sorry.

372
00:25:03,600 --> 00:25:06,640
And... cheek to cheek.

373
00:25:07,800 --> 00:25:08,840
Right.

374
00:25:11,510 --> 00:25:12,960
Cheek to cheek, please.

375
00:25:13,020 --> 00:25:13,880
Yeah.

376
00:25:23,400 --> 00:25:24,840
May Grandpa and Grandma

377
00:25:25,280 --> 00:25:26,680
love each other for a long time.

378
00:25:28,640 --> 00:25:29,920
Stay strong.

379
00:25:34,500 --> 00:25:38,400
The time of happiness usually
comes and goes, Grandpa, Grandma.

380
00:25:38,540 --> 00:25:42,280
But you've experienced happiness
in marriage twice already.

381
00:25:43,080 --> 00:25:44,760
It's considered a bonus, you know?

382
00:25:46,080 --> 00:25:48,400
Thank you so much to both of you.

383
00:25:48,780 --> 00:25:50,360
Getting married again makes me feel

384
00:25:50,380 --> 00:25:53,280
fitter and stronger
in the blink of an eye.

385
00:25:56,020 --> 00:25:57,920
I love you, you know?

386
00:25:58,200 --> 00:26:00,800
My love for you is still
the same as always.

387
00:26:00,830 --> 00:26:03,850
How can it be the same?
Hasn't it grown at all?

388
00:26:03,880 --> 00:26:05,690
It's fully grown.

389
00:26:05,720 --> 00:26:07,160
So full you can't even breathe, huh?

390
00:26:08,960 --> 00:26:09,600
Well,

391
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:12,560
you two should also remember that

392
00:26:12,980 --> 00:26:14,840
during happy times,

393
00:26:15,240 --> 00:26:17,000
you should enjoy every moment

394
00:26:17,580 --> 00:26:19,210
so that when trouble comes,

395
00:26:19,240 --> 00:26:21,240
you'll remember

396
00:26:21,270 --> 00:26:24,340
how happy you were together, okay?

397
00:27:22,600 --> 00:27:23,680
Good job, everyone.

398
00:27:23,840 --> 00:27:25,960
You did much better
with the new move we added yesterday.

399
00:27:26,100 --> 00:27:27,640
Of course, Pitcha.

400
00:27:27,670 --> 00:27:30,090
If we're training this hard
and still don't improve,

401
00:27:30,120 --> 00:27:31,800
we shouldn't dance anymore.

402
00:27:32,020 --> 00:27:32,760
Good job.

403
00:27:32,790 --> 00:27:34,920
"Practice makes perfect."

404
00:27:36,400 --> 00:27:38,480
You're tired, right?
Let's take a break, shall we?

405
00:27:45,760 --> 00:27:46,880
Hey, guys!

406
00:27:46,940 --> 00:27:47,880
Ploy, look.

407
00:27:48,020 --> 00:27:50,800
The contest we sent a video to last week

408
00:27:51,000 --> 00:27:52,280
sent us a message that...

409
00:27:53,080 --> 00:27:54,920
we passed!

410
00:27:56,880 --> 00:27:59,160
- Let me see it!
- Here.

411
00:27:59,300 --> 00:28:00,630
We need your help, Pitcha.

412
00:28:00,660 --> 00:28:02,410
We need you to help us create a new show.

413
00:28:02,440 --> 00:28:04,440
You must not say no.

414
00:28:04,470 --> 00:28:07,920
Without you, we won't know what to do.

415
00:28:09,380 --> 00:28:10,160
Of course.

416
00:28:10,400 --> 00:28:12,080
I'll do my best to help you,

417
00:28:12,320 --> 00:28:13,720
but you need to do your best, too.
Okay?

418
00:28:13,960 --> 00:28:15,400
We promise.

419
00:28:15,540 --> 00:28:17,400
Great. So, today,

420
00:28:17,460 --> 00:28:19,000
go home to get enough rest,

421
00:28:19,140 --> 00:28:21,480
and let me know your ideas tomorrow.

422
00:28:21,760 --> 00:28:23,880
Then we're going to start with that, okay?

423
00:28:24,640 --> 00:28:26,320
Yes, Pitcha.

424
00:28:50,640 --> 00:28:51,840
What are you doing?

425
00:28:54,120 --> 00:28:55,520
As Grandpa said,

426
00:28:56,580 --> 00:28:58,400
"When we are happy together,

427
00:28:59,380 --> 00:29:00,840
we should enjoy every moment of it."

428
00:29:02,460 --> 00:29:04,560
I want to hold you like this forever.

429
00:29:10,380 --> 00:29:11,800
What if one day,

430
00:29:13,240 --> 00:29:14,520
I did something bad?

431
00:29:16,240 --> 00:29:18,440
If I let you down or hurt your feelings,

432
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:22,860
would you still hold me like this?

433
00:29:25,660 --> 00:29:29,330
♫Is it pure coincidence?♫

434
00:29:29,360 --> 00:29:30,240
You?

435
00:29:31,100 --> 00:29:32,780
What could you possibly do to let me down?

436
00:29:34,380 --> 00:29:35,780
I can't imagine...

437
00:29:36,760 --> 00:29:38,430
you could do something like that.

438
00:29:41,000 --> 00:29:42,160
Just imagine.

439
00:29:42,660 --> 00:29:43,680
Just in case.

440
00:29:46,620 --> 00:29:47,400
I'm not gonna tell you yet.

441
00:29:48,880 --> 00:29:51,640
When it's time, you'll know...

442
00:29:52,560 --> 00:29:53,760
how I deal with it.

443
00:29:58,200 --> 00:29:59,560
Why are you making that face?

444
00:30:01,280 --> 00:30:03,040
Now, everything is fine.

445
00:30:04,220 --> 00:30:06,220
Why think about the future?

446
00:30:09,440 --> 00:30:15,520
♫I believe our love will change our♫

447
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:20,610
♫Destiny, rewrite prophecies♫

448
00:30:20,640 --> 00:30:25,450
♫Even if they are against our destiny♫

449
00:30:25,480 --> 00:30:29,010
♫(But we're gonna try, try, try)♫

450
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:49,920
Please come in.
Have you reserved a table yet?

451
00:30:51,080 --> 00:30:53,610
Does Ritt, the Prophecy Stone Master,
come today?

452
00:30:53,640 --> 00:30:56,440
Oh, Ritt won't come here today.

453
00:31:00,520 --> 00:31:01,640
That's too bad.

454
00:31:02,160 --> 00:31:03,840
If you would like to have your fortune read,

455
00:31:04,020 --> 00:31:06,280
Ployplern, the Pictura Master,
is glad to assist you.

456
00:31:08,280 --> 00:31:09,320
I'll give it a try.

457
00:31:10,400 --> 00:31:12,520
Maybe there will be some answers
that can put my mind at rest.

458
00:31:18,560 --> 00:31:20,280
Take a deep breath.

459
00:31:20,520 --> 00:31:21,920
Stay focused.

460
00:31:22,020 --> 00:31:24,720
Think of things you want to know,
then pick three cards.

461
00:31:40,760 --> 00:31:41,840
The first card:

462
00:31:42,980 --> 00:31:45,600
a secret hidden in the dark.

463
00:31:50,140 --> 00:31:51,340
The second card:

464
00:31:52,220 --> 00:31:55,720
a restraint
that prevents you from speaking up.

465
00:31:58,140 --> 00:31:59,240
The third card:

466
00:32:04,320 --> 00:32:06,200
a major change.

467
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:08,840
The things you're going to do

468
00:32:09,370 --> 00:32:12,480
will reveal something important

469
00:32:12,700 --> 00:32:14,840
that leads to a change in you.

470
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:16,920
Of course,

471
00:32:18,060 --> 00:32:20,400
there must be some changes.

472
00:32:24,160 --> 00:32:25,640
It's time for the truth

473
00:32:26,340 --> 00:32:27,960
to come to light.

474
00:32:36,760 --> 00:32:40,090
Contemporary house design,

475
00:32:40,120 --> 00:32:43,520
which is a combination
of energy stones and runes,

476
00:32:43,920 --> 00:32:48,080
offers not only physical comfort

477
00:32:48,200 --> 00:32:51,080
but also builds new meanings,

478
00:32:51,480 --> 00:32:53,050
a sense of safety,

479
00:32:53,080 --> 00:32:56,530
and balanced energy for the residents

480
00:32:56,560 --> 00:32:58,080
in a contemporary context.

481
00:32:58,180 --> 00:33:00,970
Hello, well... My house design

482
00:33:01,000 --> 00:33:02,490
is like this.

483
00:33:02,520 --> 00:33:03,760
There is a chimney on top.

484
00:33:04,720 --> 00:33:08,420
Okay, my piece is about the bedroom.

485
00:33:08,450 --> 00:33:10,160
It's at the back because...

486
00:33:18,560 --> 00:33:19,600
Well done, Ritt.

487
00:33:22,760 --> 00:33:24,880
For today...
you did a great job, everyone.

488
00:33:25,100 --> 00:33:26,700
See you next time.

489
00:33:28,140 --> 00:33:28,960
Go home.

490
00:33:29,560 --> 00:33:30,360
That's it.

491
00:33:31,080 --> 00:33:33,010
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

492
00:33:33,040 --> 00:33:33,880
Thank you.

493
00:33:39,640 --> 00:33:41,120
Hey! Ritt.

494
00:33:42,240 --> 00:33:43,760
Are you free next week?

495
00:33:44,760 --> 00:33:45,490
Yes, professor.

496
00:33:45,520 --> 00:33:49,000
Here is the thing: I would like you
to go to a restaurant,

497
00:33:49,640 --> 00:33:51,330
which is my student's,

498
00:33:51,360 --> 00:33:52,720
your senior.

499
00:33:53,520 --> 00:33:56,280
Their space planning

500
00:33:56,840 --> 00:33:58,600
is based on the concept of land breeze

501
00:33:59,640 --> 00:34:00,560
and sea breeze.

502
00:34:01,360 --> 00:34:02,440
The coming in

503
00:34:03,040 --> 00:34:04,600
and the pulling back of waves.

504
00:34:05,360 --> 00:34:08,920
I think there are
some similarities in your work.

505
00:34:10,239 --> 00:34:11,320
That's great, professor.

506
00:34:11,679 --> 00:34:13,469
I'm going to call them

507
00:34:13,520 --> 00:34:14,800
to find out what day they'll be there,

508
00:34:15,239 --> 00:34:18,440
so they can explain
the concept of its design.

509
00:34:18,880 --> 00:34:19,679
Does that sound good?

510
00:34:20,500 --> 00:34:21,560
Yes, professor.

511
00:34:21,679 --> 00:34:22,760
See you later.

512
00:34:23,380 --> 00:34:24,280
Goodbye.

513
00:34:32,000 --> 00:34:35,080
[Unknown number:
See you at the usual place]

514
00:35:18,080 --> 00:35:19,280
I thought you were not going to come.

515
00:35:21,840 --> 00:35:24,400
Have...we known each other before?

516
00:35:25,420 --> 00:35:26,520
Does it matter

517
00:35:27,360 --> 00:35:28,500
whether you know me

518
00:35:29,340 --> 00:35:30,360
or not,

519
00:35:31,340 --> 00:35:34,440
since you
can just impersonate others, can't you?

520
00:35:38,400 --> 00:35:39,400
What do you want?

521
00:35:40,100 --> 00:35:41,380
I want nothing.

522
00:35:42,240 --> 00:35:43,760
I just want to help you...

523
00:35:44,040 --> 00:35:46,720
maintain that fake happiness
for a long time.

524
00:35:47,400 --> 00:35:48,560
What did you know?

525
00:35:49,840 --> 00:35:51,280
I know everything.

526
00:35:51,800 --> 00:35:54,200
I know whose sweetheart
you are pretending to be.

527
00:35:55,800 --> 00:35:58,400
On top of that, you deprived
the lovers of each other.

528
00:36:00,220 --> 00:36:01,240
You're smart, aren't you?

529
00:36:01,940 --> 00:36:03,240
You shouldn't study architecture.

530
00:36:04,080 --> 00:36:05,360
You should study...

531
00:36:06,400 --> 00:36:07,400
how to make up stories

532
00:36:07,960 --> 00:36:09,200
or fiction writing.

533
00:36:10,030 --> 00:36:11,920
Tons of people might
look forward to reading it.

534
00:36:15,120 --> 00:36:16,160
Tell me what you want.

535
00:36:18,120 --> 00:36:19,160
Five hundred thousand baht.

536
00:36:20,240 --> 00:36:20,960
What?!

537
00:36:22,080 --> 00:36:23,240
Five hundred thousand?!

538
00:36:24,420 --> 00:36:25,560
I don't have that much money.

539
00:36:26,160 --> 00:36:27,160
Also,

540
00:36:28,120 --> 00:36:30,120
I intend to tell the whole truth.

541
00:36:30,660 --> 00:36:32,040
Wow,

542
00:36:33,380 --> 00:36:35,600
the time of happiness is about
to be over, isn't it?

543
00:36:36,920 --> 00:36:38,440
That's so unfortunate.

544
00:36:41,100 --> 00:36:42,960
I haven't taken part yet.

545
00:36:45,520 --> 00:36:47,120
What you are doing right now

546
00:36:48,920 --> 00:36:50,520
is clearly extortion.

547
00:36:51,160 --> 00:36:53,360
And what will you call
the thing you're doing?

548
00:36:54,340 --> 00:36:54,960
Huh?

549
00:36:56,660 --> 00:36:59,920
What do you think
will happen if more people find out?

550
00:37:00,720 --> 00:37:01,600
From one...

551
00:37:02,680 --> 00:37:03,680
to two...

552
00:37:04,880 --> 00:37:05,800
to three...

553
00:37:07,480 --> 00:37:08,720
What do you think will happen?

554
00:37:11,400 --> 00:37:13,560
"Master Ritt Abuses His Position

555
00:37:13,960 --> 00:37:15,960
Using Sacred Means

556
00:37:16,760 --> 00:37:18,240
for Personal Gain."

557
00:37:19,460 --> 00:37:21,880
And what if Itthi or Pitcha finds out?

558
00:37:26,240 --> 00:37:27,360
I don't even want to think about it.

559
00:37:28,720 --> 00:37:29,920
What are your thoughts...

560
00:37:31,760 --> 00:37:33,240
on Itthi's feeling

561
00:37:33,960 --> 00:37:35,760
for having been as stupid
as a donkey for so long?

562
00:37:36,900 --> 00:37:38,480
Can he have you arrested?

563
00:37:39,980 --> 00:37:42,080
And what will you be charged with?

564
00:37:43,560 --> 00:37:45,240
What if Pitcha finds out?

565
00:37:47,040 --> 00:37:48,760
You actually stole
a celebrity's boyfriend.

566
00:37:50,620 --> 00:37:53,040
What if people
at the university find out...

567
00:37:56,780 --> 00:38:00,480
It might reflect badly on
your professional ethics as a future architect.

568
00:38:01,160 --> 00:38:04,580
And who's going to hire
a swindler like you as an architect, huh?

569
00:38:12,520 --> 00:38:13,760
But I don't have

570
00:38:15,040 --> 00:38:15,800
that much money.

571
00:38:17,580 --> 00:38:18,960
Ask Itthi for it!

572
00:38:20,540 --> 00:38:22,340
He is so into you, isn't he?

573
00:38:23,920 --> 00:38:25,920
For a multibillionaire like him,

574
00:38:27,040 --> 00:38:28,160
this little amount of money

575
00:38:29,070 --> 00:38:30,760
shouldn't cause him any trouble.

576
00:39:05,160 --> 00:39:05,880
I'll be back.

577
00:39:10,780 --> 00:39:12,360
Why are you making that face?

578
00:39:17,160 --> 00:39:18,180
The Korean agency

579
00:39:19,020 --> 00:39:20,140
sent me a message.

580
00:39:21,880 --> 00:39:24,120
They told me to go back
to auditioning for a new project.

581
00:39:28,100 --> 00:39:29,780
Well, that's nice, right?

582
00:39:30,700 --> 00:39:32,700
This is a good opportunity for you,

583
00:39:33,780 --> 00:39:36,580
so you can return to doing what you love.

584
00:39:42,280 --> 00:39:43,120
You think so?

585
00:39:47,000 --> 00:39:47,840
Why?

586
00:39:48,160 --> 00:39:50,480
Don't you want to go back?

587
00:39:54,300 --> 00:39:55,540
I don't know either.

588
00:39:56,680 --> 00:39:58,120
Now, I feel like

589
00:39:58,640 --> 00:40:00,160
the dream I had

590
00:40:02,040 --> 00:40:03,400
is starting to change.

591
00:40:10,980 --> 00:40:12,200
Is that because of me?

592
00:40:21,960 --> 00:40:23,680
I thought you were going to tell me...

593
00:40:24,020 --> 00:40:25,200
to stay here

594
00:40:25,400 --> 00:40:26,740
and not go back to the audition.

595
00:40:32,440 --> 00:40:33,750
Actually...

596
00:40:33,840 --> 00:40:36,020
I wanted to say that,

597
00:40:38,180 --> 00:40:40,840
but it would probably be too selfish of me.

598
00:40:43,720 --> 00:40:46,640
You have a dream waiting for you there.

599
00:40:49,240 --> 00:40:53,080
This place might be too small
to make your big dream come true.

600
00:40:58,620 --> 00:40:59,840
And I'm just...

601
00:41:01,000 --> 00:41:02,560
a small bar owner,

602
00:41:03,200 --> 00:41:04,720
who can only be...

603
00:41:05,560 --> 00:41:07,400
your fan at best

604
00:41:14,160 --> 00:41:15,640
You're a bit too far from me.

605
00:41:17,040 --> 00:41:19,040
I don't even dare to reach out
and make you stay.

606
00:41:26,920 --> 00:41:28,320
Don't you want to try?

607
00:41:29,720 --> 00:41:31,040
I'm not like you.

608
00:41:32,480 --> 00:41:34,360
You've been trying for so long.

609
00:41:35,120 --> 00:41:35,680
And...

610
00:41:36,760 --> 00:41:39,800
it's going to pay off soon.

611
00:41:43,040 --> 00:41:44,160
But for me...

612
00:41:46,560 --> 00:41:47,880
it's wrong just to think about it.

613
00:41:51,920 --> 00:41:52,760
What do you think?

614
00:41:55,840 --> 00:41:56,840
Thank you so much.

615
00:41:59,440 --> 00:42:01,040
If I go back to live there,

616
00:42:04,480 --> 00:42:06,200
I will definitely miss this place a lot.

617
00:42:11,360 --> 00:42:12,600
After you make your debut,

618
00:42:12,920 --> 00:42:14,920
you probably can't come
to a place like this.

619
00:42:16,240 --> 00:42:18,040
Or if you can, you might...

620
00:42:18,380 --> 00:42:20,430
have many guards around you.

621
00:42:22,280 --> 00:42:23,360
Perhaps

622
00:42:24,000 --> 00:42:25,560
next time you come back,

623
00:42:26,320 --> 00:42:28,000
you probably won't remember me anymore.

624
00:42:37,740 --> 00:42:38,440
What?

625
00:42:41,400 --> 00:42:42,600
I gave you my promise.

626
00:42:43,960 --> 00:42:44,960
No matter what,

627
00:42:45,800 --> 00:42:46,850
I'm going to come back.

628
00:43:22,200 --> 00:43:23,100
Are you hurt, Grandma?

629
00:43:23,140 --> 00:43:24,620
Ugh. No, I'm not.

630
00:43:28,250 --> 00:43:30,040
Coming home so late, huh, Ritt?

631
00:43:32,820 --> 00:43:34,340
Itthi is waiting for you.

632
00:43:34,400 --> 00:43:36,010
He said he had something to talk to you.

633
00:43:36,080 --> 00:43:37,620
I told him to call you, but he didn't.

634
00:43:37,660 --> 00:43:39,880
He said he wanted
to talk to you in person.

635
00:43:41,240 --> 00:43:42,280
What's the matter?

636
00:43:42,460 --> 00:43:44,160
Oh, I don't know either.

637
00:43:44,440 --> 00:43:46,240
Just go upstairs to talk to him yourself.

638
00:43:48,280 --> 00:43:49,120
Yes, Grandma.

639
00:44:07,580 --> 00:44:08,440
Are you sleeping?

640
00:44:17,840 --> 00:44:19,360
Who should I tell the truth to first?

641
00:44:22,360 --> 00:44:25,200
How about I start with the people
who came to you for fortune readings,

642
00:44:25,980 --> 00:44:28,200
then your professors,

643
00:44:28,620 --> 00:44:30,620
and post it on social media

644
00:44:31,960 --> 00:44:33,240
and tag Pitcha

645
00:44:34,520 --> 00:44:36,480
and Itthiphumi Pongpanyalert?

646
00:44:39,340 --> 00:44:40,760
I'll give you time to think...

647
00:44:42,200 --> 00:44:43,200
for three days.

648
00:44:44,480 --> 00:44:47,480
And after that, I don't know who will be
the first to find out the truth.

649
00:44:48,000 --> 00:44:50,640
Last time, you were famous for being
Ritt, the Prophecy Stone Master.

650
00:44:51,680 --> 00:44:53,680
This time, let me name you in advance.

651
00:44:55,080 --> 00:44:55,840
Ritt...

652
00:44:56,600 --> 00:44:57,680
the Fraud Master.

653
00:45:00,740 --> 00:45:03,400
I have no idea what you are asking me,

654
00:45:06,260 --> 00:45:08,260
but if it's time to say it,

655
00:45:09,120 --> 00:45:11,120
I'm going to tell you the truth.

656
00:45:13,400 --> 00:45:14,800
But just do me one favor.

657
00:45:18,400 --> 00:45:19,760
Please don't hate me.

658
00:45:23,160 --> 00:45:24,760
I never intended to deceive you

659
00:45:26,400 --> 00:45:28,400
with anything that I did.

660
00:45:30,480 --> 00:45:33,400
But I did it because
I love you so much.

661
00:45:36,480 --> 00:45:38,720
I wanted to be the apple of your eye,

662
00:45:40,680 --> 00:45:41,880
close to you,

663
00:45:42,920 --> 00:45:44,320
and the person you loved.

664
00:45:58,480 --> 00:45:59,620
I'm so sorry.

665
00:46:51,160 --> 00:46:52,840
You saw the photo I sent you, right?

666
00:46:54,440 --> 00:46:55,560
They finally met each other.

667
00:46:56,320 --> 00:46:58,040
Well, this issue...

668
00:46:58,860 --> 00:47:00,280
Did you know from the beginning

669
00:47:01,520 --> 00:47:03,440
that I wasn't your childhood sweetheart?

670
00:47:04,780 --> 00:47:06,120
Liars like us,

671
00:47:07,040 --> 00:47:09,000
who love to make up stories,

672
00:47:09,560 --> 00:47:10,920
aren't supposed to be together.

673
00:47:13,320 --> 00:47:15,000
The more I look at you...

674
00:47:16,680 --> 00:47:17,760
the more I want to know you.

675
00:47:29,560 --> 00:47:33,360
♫Is it pure coincidence?♫

676
00:47:33,610 --> 00:47:37,680
♫Or is it destiny that decides?♫

677
00:47:37,710 --> 00:47:40,020
♫Is someone above drawing all these lines?♫

678
00:47:40,040 --> 00:47:45,560
♫Or playing matchmaker in disguise?♫

679
00:47:46,180 --> 00:47:50,380
♫What if the stars shift in their place♫

680
00:47:50,570 --> 00:47:54,050
♫Slightly out of line,♫

681
00:47:54,810 --> 00:47:58,500
♫Will our orbits still align?♫

682
00:47:58,530 --> 00:48:02,840
♫Try answering if your world
will cross with mine♫

683
00:48:02,870 --> 00:48:06,920
♫Though the destiny between us
is differently defined♫

684
00:48:06,950 --> 00:48:12,250
♫I believe our love will change our♫

685
00:48:12,560 --> 00:48:16,410
♫Destiny, rewrite prophecies♫

686
00:48:16,460 --> 00:48:20,510
♫Even if they are against our destiny♫

687
00:48:20,540 --> 00:48:23,250
♫(But we're gonna try, try, try)♫

688
00:48:23,290 --> 00:48:29,050
♫And I believe our love has power♫

689
00:48:29,100 --> 00:48:32,900
♫I believe the love of us♫

690
00:48:32,930 --> 00:48:41,000
♫Will realign the stars back to the line
where they should be♫

691
00:48:41,030 --> 00:48:44,170
♫(And we're gonna try, try, try)♫

